The paper deals with information concentration in probability measures, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. However, the use of log-concave distributions and exp-concave potentials suggests that the paper is most likely to be classified under Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of the variance Brascamp-Lieb inequality suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of Data Structures (cs.DS), Scientific Computing (cs.SI), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
